---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import HeroSection from '../components/HeroSection.astro';
---

<Layout title="Clients" description="Explore our strategic and delivery clients in the space sector.">
  <Header />

  <main class="py-12 max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4">
    <HeroSection 
      title="Our Impact" 
      description="Driving positive change through purpose-led digital strategy, data ethics, and sustainable innovation in the space sector." 
    />

<section class="section bg-light">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Purpose Beyond Profit</h2>
    <p>At Green Orbit Digital, our work is rooted in purpose. We partner with organisations across the space industry that are building a better future—from sustainable Earth observation to circular satellite design. As a B Corp-influenced agency, every campaign is a vehicle for systems change.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Our Measurable Impact</h2>

    <ul class="impact-stats">
      <li>
        <h3>📊 65% Average Engagement Lift</h3>
        <p>Across our SEO and content-led campaigns, clients report up to 65% increases in targeted engagement.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>🌍 100% Sustainable-Focused Client Base</h3>
        <p>Every organisation we support contributes to environmental, social, or space sustainability goals.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>🔁 Circularity in Action</h3>
        <p>We actively support circular economy initiatives—helping space startups communicate lifecycle reuse, repair, and deorbiting strategies.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>🛰 Aligned with <a href="/sdgs">Space4SDGs</a></h3>
        <p>Our strategies are mapped to the UN’s Sustainable Development Goals—particularly SDG 9 (Industry, Innovation & Infrastructure), SDG 12 (Responsible Consumption), and SDG 13 (Climate Action).</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h3>🛠 Open Tools for Impact</h3>
        <p>We build and share open-source tools to calculate digital emissions, visualise sustainability metrics, and support responsible data use.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section bg-light">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Advancing Sustainable Marketing</h2>
    <p>Our impact isn't just what we deliver—it's how we operate. From carbon-aware hosting and energy-efficient code to ethical analytics, we walk the talk:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Carbon-Aware Hosting:</strong> Our sites are hosted on green infrastructure using providers that match or exceed our own digital sustainability standards.</li>
      <li><strong>Data Minimisation:</strong> We apply privacy-by-design principles, using tools like Plausible and Matomo for ethical analytics.</li>
      <li><strong>Digital Emissions Auditing:</strong> Every campaign includes an emissions review using our in-house CO₂ audit scripts and batch tools.</li>
      <li><strong>Low-Carbon Design:</strong> Our sites are built to perform fast on low bandwidth—improving UX while reducing unnecessary resource consumption.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Shaping the Future of Space, Ethically</h2>
    <p>As Chair of the UKspace Startup Working Group, our Director actively drives the sustainability agenda within the UK’s commercial space ecosystem. We regularly speak on:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Sustainable marketing practices for NewSpace startups</li>
      <li>Responsible innovation in Earth observation</li>
      <li>SDG alignment in commercial missions</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Listen to our ongoing conversations on <a href="/podcast">The Sustainable Space Podcast</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section bg-highlight">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Let’s Build Better Together</h2>
    <p>Want to amplify your sustainability story, reduce your digital carbon footprint, or align your campaign with the SDGs?</p>
    <p><a class="button" href="/contact">Get in touch</a></p>
  </div>
</section>